## Project Overview

This is a Sovrium application. Sovrium is a configuration-driven platform where your app is defined in a YAML file and validated against a typed schema.

## Commands

```bash
# Start the development server
sovrium start app.yaml

# Start with watch mode (auto-reload on config changes)
sovrium start app.yaml --watch

# Validate config without starting
sovrium validate app.yaml

# Build static site
sovrium build app.yaml

# Print the full JSON Schema
sovrium schema

# Print schema to a file
sovrium schema --output schema.json
```

## Runtime

- **Runtime**: Bun (NOT Node.js)
- **Package manager**: Bun (`bun install`, NOT npm/yarn)
- **Config format**: YAML or JSON

## Key Files

- `app.yaml` -- Application configuration (tables, auth, pages, theme)
- `CLAUDE.md` -- This file (LLM context)

## LLM Documentation

For AI-assisted development, fetch the official Sovrium documentation optimized for LLMs:

| Resource | URL | Description |
|----------|-----|-------------|
| **llms.txt** | https://sovrium.com/llms.txt | Documentation index and quick reference |
| **llms-full.txt** | https://sovrium.com/llms-full.txt | Complete documentation (~2800 lines) |

Use `WebFetch("https://sovrium.com/llms-full.txt")` to load the full schema reference, configuration options, field types, and examples.

### Key Schema Sections

- **App metadata**: name (required), version, description
- **Tables**: Field types (40+), relationships, permissions, soft-delete
- **Pages**: Sections, components, SEO meta, interactions, responsive design
- **Theme**: Colors, fonts, spacing, shadows, borderRadius, animations, breakpoints
- **Auth**: Email/password, magic link, OAuth (8 providers), 2FA, roles
- **Languages**: i18n with translations, browser detection, persistence
- **Analytics**: First-party page view tracking
- **Components**: Reusable UI templates with variable substitution

## Tips

- Edit `app.yaml` and restart to see changes (or use `--watch` for auto-reload)
- Sovrium validates your config on every start -- check the error output for guidance
- Use `sovrium validate app.yaml` for quick validation without starting the server
- Tables require at least one field; pages require at least one section
- Auth must be configured if you use `user`, `created-by`, or `updated-by` field types
- Field names must follow PostgreSQL conventions: `^[a-z][a-z0-9_]*$` (underscores, not hyphens)
- Field types use hyphens: `single-line-text`, `created-by`, `auto-number`
